{"cursor":"2573","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Implication' is the relationship between the two statements of a conditional\nstatement A , called the antecedent and B , called the\nconsequent when A implies B .\n\nIn logic, logical consequence is a fundamental concept which is often used\nsynonymously with 'implication'. However, sometimes the term is used to\ndistinguish between:\n* '[[Logical consequence|Logical implication]]', (also 'implication' or\n  'entailment', or the 'consequence relation'), a relation between statements\n  when one A implies the other B ; and\n* '[[Material conditional |Material implication]]', (also 'material\n  conditional', 'conditional' or 'conditional implication'), a logical\n  connective and binary truth function.\n::*In propositional logic, ' material implication' is a valid rule of\n::replacement which is an instance of the connective of the same name. It is the\n::rule that states that \" P implies Q \" is logically\n::equivalent to \"not- P or Q \".\n* 'Definitional implication' -- when one statement implies another by\n  definition. (\"If Jerry is my father, then he is my son's grandfather.\")\n* 'Causal implication' -- when the relation between the antecedent and\n  consequent is discovered empirically. (\"If I put the litmus paper in acid, it\n  will turn red.\")\n* 'Decisional implication' -- when there is no logical connection nor one by\n  definition between the consequent and antecedent. This is a decision of the\n  speaker to behave in the specified way under the specified circumstances. (\"If\n  I'm wrong, I'll eat my hat.\")\n\n'Other uses':\n* In modal logic, '[[Strict conditional|strict implication]]', (also 'strict\n  conditional') is a modal connector, a logical connective of modal logic that\n  expresses necessity.\n* In linguistics, specifically in pragmatics:\n::* Implicature\n::* Entailment (pragmatics)\n* In medical diagnosis, the scientific method, and forensics, a hypothetical\n  cause is implicated or indicated when a reason for the condition can be found,\n  given that cause.\n","linknr":123,"url":"imply","recorded":1363456918,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Implication&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Implication&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Implication","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Imply&redirect=no","#mw-head","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//en.wiktionary.org/wiki/implication","/wiki/Statement_(logic)","/wiki/Conditional_sentence","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/f/c/7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29.png","/wiki/Antecedent_(logic)","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/d/5/9d5ed678fe57bcca610140957afab571.png","/wiki/Consequent","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/f/c/7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/d/5/9d5ed678fe57bcca610140957afab571.png","/wiki/Logic","/wiki/Logical_consequence","/wiki/Concept","/wiki/Logical_consequence","/wiki/Binary_relation","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/f/c/7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/d/5/9d5ed678fe57bcca610140957afab571.png","/wiki/Material_conditional","/wiki/Logical_connective","/wiki/Binary_function",